'''Aniwave''' was an annual one day anime convention held during December at the Wilmington Convention Center in [[Wilmington, North Carolina]].
==Programming== The convention typically offered a costume contest, demonstrations, panels, vendors, and workshops.<ref name="sno11162010"/><ref name="sno12082013">{{cite web|url=http://www.starnewsonline.com/article/20131208/ARTICLES/131209762|title=There's a reason to get all dressed up at Aniwave convention|publisher=Star News Online|author=Caitlin Dineen|date=December 8, 2013|accessdate=April 10, 2016}}</ref>
==History== Aniwave was founded in 2007 by artist [[Michal Wisniowski]] as an free [[film festival]] held at the [[Cameron Art Museum]] and Jengo’s Playhouse.<ref name="sno11162010"/><ref name="Encore"/><ref name="Encore2">{{citation | title=Art with Depth: Aniwave reaches an eager audience| publisher=Encore | date=October 21, 2009| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710193225/http://www.encorepub.com/a_a/blogs/blog1.php/2009/10/27/art-with-depth-aniwave-reaches-an-eager-| archivedate=July 10, 2011| url=http://www.encorepub.com/a_a/blogs/blog1.php/2009/10/27/art-with-depth-aniwave-reaches-an-eager-| accessdate=2010-07-29 }}</ref> The convention moved to a larger venue in 2010, the Wilmington Convention Center, and had new leadership due to Michal Wisniowski moving away.<ref name="sno11162010"/>
