'''Hole in the Sky''' was a Norwegian [[extreme metal]] festival located in [[Bergen]] that took place at the end of August each year from 2000 to 2011.<ref>http://www.ba.no/puls/musikk/article5558381.ece</ref> The first event was held in 2000 in honor of the then recently deceased [[Erik Brødreskift|Erik "Grim" Brødreskift]], ex-member of [[Borknagar]], [[Gorgoroth]] and [[Immortal (band)|Immortal]].<ref>http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/distrikt/hordaland/1.7585883</ref> The festival was named after the [[Hole in the Sky (song)|eponymous song]] by [[Black Sabbath]].

