{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox recurring event |name = International Festival of Comics |image = |location=[[Algiers]], [[Algeria]] |genre=[[Comics]] |years_active=2008-present |website= [http://www.bdalger.net/ Official website] }}
'''The International Festival of Comics''' (Festival International de la Bande Dessinée d’Alger, FIBDA)<ref name=wwb>{{cite web|title=A Dispatch from FIDBA, the International Comics Festival of Algeria|url=http://wordswithoutborders.org/dispatches/article/a-dispatch-from-fidba-the-international-comics-festival-of-algeria|work=Words without Borders|accessdate=17 January 2014|author=Canan Marasligil|date=17 October 2011}}</ref> is a thematic festival organized in [[Algiers]], [[Algeria]], which was launched in 2008.
==History and profile== The FIBDA was established in Algiers, Algeria, in 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Swimming against the Tide|url=http://en.qantara.de/content/comics-artists-in-the-arab-world-swimming-against-the-tide|accessdate=17 January 2014|work=Qantara|date=18 July 2012|author=Charlotte Bank}}</ref> It takes place in October annually under the aegis of the Ministry of Culture.<ref name=bc>{{cite web|title=International Festival of Comics of Algeria (FIBDA)|url=http://literature.britishcouncil.org/international-festival-of-comics-of-algeria-fibda|work=British Council|accessdate=17 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=aps>{{cite news|title=2nd International Festival of Comics|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-212389458.html|accessdate=17 January 2014|work=Algeria Press Service|date=16 October 2009|location=Algiers}}{{Subscription required|via=HighBeam}}</ref> In 2011, [[French people|French]] cartoonist Hervé Barulea became the president of the FIBDA.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Mark McKinney|title=Interview with Baru: Part 1|journal=European Comic Art|date=1 July 2011|volume=4|issue=2|url=https://www.questia.com/read/1P3-2532411021/interview-with-baru-part-1|accessdate=17 January 2014}}{{Subscription required|via=Questia}}</ref>
The focus of the FIBDA is the [[comic book industry]].<ref name=bc/> It has annual themes - for instance, it was "Algiers, Balloons Bay" in 2009<ref name=aps/> and “Algiers, Bubbles Without Borders” in 2011.<ref name=wwb/> Artists from different countries in addition to local artists participate in the events organized under the FIBDA.<ref name=wwb/><ref>{{cite web|title=International Festival of the Comic|url=http://www.algeria.com/blog/international-festival-of-the-comic|work=Algeria.com|accessdate=17 January 2014}}</ref> Therefore, it is the major event in its category in pan [[Africa]] and [[Arab world]] with its huge number of international guests and its activities.<ref>{{cite web|title=ASIFA Egypt delegation to "FIBDA" Algeria's Comics Festival|url=http://egypt.asifa.net/|work=ASIFA|accessdate=17 January 2014|date=18 October 2012}}</ref> In the festival several bodies and publications focusing on comics from Africa are awarded.<ref name=wwb/><ref name=ahr>{{cite news|title=Award-winning TokTok magazine celebrates first anniversary|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/5/35/32210/Arts--Culture/Stage--Street/Awardwinning-TokTok-magazine-celebrates-first-anni.aspx|accessdate=17 January 2014|work=Ahram Online|date=20 January 2012}}</ref> One of the publications awarded is the Egyptian magazine ''[[Tok Tok]]''.<ref name=ahr/>
