{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Weekly'' (news magazine)}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}
'''''Weekly''''' is an English-language national [[news magazine]] published by the La Sentinelle Group in [[Mauritius]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lasentinelle.mu/spip.php?article90|title=La Sentinelle|website=La Sentinelle|accessdate=11 September 2016}}</ref> The magazine, which only exists on paper and direct-email [[Portable Document Format|PDF]], has a relatively low readership, but is considered one of the most important sources of political news on the island.{{by whom|date=September 2016}} The magazine is known both for its news reporting, as well as its critical and often mocking editorials.

==History and profile==
It was started as a weekly section, named Outlook, of ''[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]]'' newspaper.<ref name="nir">{{cite journal|author=Nirmal Kumar Betchoo|title=French language in Mauritian newspapers: A Cultural Exception in Journalism|journal=International Journal for Research in Social Science and Humanities Research|date=February 2016|volume=2|issue=2|url=http://internationaljournalsforresearch.com/Pdf/International%20Journal%20for%20Research%20in%20Social%20Science%20and%20Humanities%20Research/International%20Journal%20for%20Research%20in%20Social%20Science%20and%20Humanities%20Research-Feb-7.pdf|accessdate=4 December 2016}}</ref> It became a weekly magazine in July 2012.<ref name="nir"/> The magazine is published on Fridays.<ref name="nir"/> The [[editor-in-chief]], Touria Prayag, was temporarily banned from [[Parliament of Mauritius|Mauritian Parliament]] in 2016 by its speaker, [[Maya Hanoomanjee]], because of a critical editorial published in ''Weekly'' on 28 April 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lexpress.mu/article/283584/apres-un-editorial-touria-prayag-interdite-dacces-au-parlement|title=Après un éditorial: Touria Prayag interdite d'accès au Parlement|last=Deena|first=Manisha|date=14 June 2016|work=|publisher=La Sentinelle|newspaper=L'Express|access-date=11 September 2016}}</ref>

